  "A person has three debts: Credit card ($3,000 at 22%), car loan ($15,000 at 6%), and student loan ($25,000 at 4.5%). Using the avalanche method, which order should they pay extra on?": "",
  "Student loan, car loan, credit card": "",
  "Student loan, credit card, car loan": "",
  "Car loan, student loan, credit card": "",
  "Credit card (22%), then car loan (6%), then student loan (4.5%)": "",
  "The avalanche method targets the highest interest rate first: credit card (22%) first, then car loan (6%), then student loan (4.5%). This minimizes total interest paid. Make minimum payments on all debts while putting extra money toward the highest-rate one.": "",
