  "NPV = $54,076 - $50,000 = +$4,076. Since NPV is positive, the equipment earns more than the 12% required return. The investment creates $4,076 in value above what could be earned at the discount rate.": "",
  "Portfolio X returns 14% with 22% standard deviation. Portfolio Y returns 9% with 10% standard deviation. Risk-free rate is 4%. Which portfolio is better on a risk-adjusted basis?": "",
  "Portfolio X — higher absolute return": "",
  "Portfolio Y — Sharpe of 0.50": "",
  "Portfolio X — Sharpe of 0.45": "",
  "They are equal": "",
  "Portfolio X Sharpe = (14 - 4) / 22 = 0.45. Portfolio Y Sharpe = (9 - 4) / 10 = 0.50. Portfolio Y delivers more excess return per unit of risk. Higher absolute returns do not necessarily mean better investing — risk-adjustment reveals the true picture.": "",
